{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon, Original Serialized Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-15",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/maltesefalcon_2511_librivox/maltesefalcon_15_hammett.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Chapter 15 - Officials",
  "reader_name": "Mark Nelson",
  "page_num": 5,
  "page_total": 6,
  "page_start_sec": 982.28,
  "page_end_sec": 1222.98,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.734,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 982.28,
      "end": 984.3,
      "text": "But I heard that Thursby took Monaghan",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 984.3,
      "end": 985.86,
      "text": "out to the Orient and lost him."
    },
    {
      "start": 987.648,
      "end": 991.22,
      "text": "Again the district attorney and his assistant exchanged glances.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 991.5,
      "end": 991.648,
      "text": "Thomas,"
    },
    {
      "start": 992.92,
      "end": 995.0,
      "text": "in a tone whose striving for matter-of",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 995.0,
      "end": 996.86,
      "text": "-factness did not quite hide excitement,"
    },
    {
      "start": 996.96,
      "end": 997.22,
      "text": "said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 998.368,
      "end": 999.66,
      "text": "That opens another angle.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1000.672,
      "end": 1002.1,
      "text": "Monaghan's friends could have knocked",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1002.1,
      "end": 1003.8,
      "text": "Thursby off for ditching Monaghan."
    },
    {
      "start": 1005.312,
      "end": 1007.08,
      "text": "Dead gamblers don't have any friends,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1007.46,
      "end": 1008.3,
      "text": "Spade said."
    },
    {
      "start": 1010.2,
      "end": 1011.94,
      "text": "It opens up two new lines,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1012.28,
      "end": 1013.1,
      "text": "Brian said."
    },
    {
      "start": 1013.66,
      "end": 1016.92,
      "text": "He leaned back and stared at the ceiling for several seconds,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1017.16,
      "end": 1018.78,
      "text": "then sat upright quickly."
    },
    {
      "start": 1019.2,
      "end": 1021.62,
      "text": "His orator's face was alight."
    },
    {
      "start": 1022.24,
      "end": 1024.68,
      "text": "It narrows it down to three things now."
    },
    {
      "start": 1025.632,
      "end": 1026.08,
      "text": "Number one,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1026.36,
      "end": 1028.32,
      "text": "Thursby was killed by the gamblers"
    },
    {
      "start": 1028.32,
      "end": 1030.12,
      "text": "Monaghan had welshed on in Chicago."
    },
    {
      "start": 1031.88,
      "end": 1033.8,
      "text": "Not knowing Thursby had ditched Monaghan,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1033.94,
      "end": 1035.04,
      "text": "or not believing it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1035.42,
      "end": 1038.1,
      "text": "they killed him because he had been Monaghan's associate,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1038.88,
      "end": 1041.31,
      "text": "or to get him out of the way so they could get at Monaghan,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1041.92,
      "end": 1044.28,
      "text": "or because he had refused to lead them to Monaghan."
    },
    {
      "start": 1045.472,
      "end": 1046.02,
      "text": "Number two,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1046.46,
      "end": 1048.12,
      "text": "he was killed by friends of Monaghan,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1049.0,
      "end": 1049.88,
      "text": "Or number three,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1049.98,
      "end": 1052.26,
      "text": "he sold Monaghan out to his enemies"
    },
    {
      "start": 1052.26,
      "end": 1054.06,
      "text": "and then fell out with them and they"
    },
    {
      "start": 1054.2,
      "end": 1054.62,
      "text": "killed him."
    },
    {
      "start": 1056.2,
      "end": 1057.22,
      "text": "Or number four,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1057.38,
      "end": 1059.62,
      "text": "Spade suggested with a cheerful smile,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1060.42,
      "end": 1061.66,
      "text": "he died of old age.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1062.6,
      "end": 1063.68,
      "text": "You folks aren't serious,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1063.84,
      "end": 1064.22,
      "text": "are you?"
    },
    {
      "start": 1065.44,
      "end": 1067.1,
      "text": "The two men stared at Spade,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1067.16,
      "end": 1068.52,
      "text": "but neither of them spoke."
    },
    {
      "start": 1069.76,
      "end": 1071.7,
      "text": "Spade turned his smile from one of them to",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1071.7,
      "end": 1073.92,
      "text": "the other and shook his head in mock pity."
    },
    {
      "start": 1075.776,
      "end": 1078.64,
      "text": "\"'You've got Arnold Rothstein on the brain,' he said.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1080.16,
      "end": 1081.68,
      "text": "Brian smacked the back of his right",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1081.68,
      "end": 1083.52,
      "text": "hand down into the palm of his left."
    },
    {
      "start": 1085.12,
      "end": 1088.44,
      "text": "\"'In one of those three categories lies the solution.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1089.04,
      "end": 1091.9,
      "text": "The power in his voice was no longer latent."
    },
    {
      "start": 1092.82,
      "end": 1093.7,
      "text": "His right hand,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1093.74,
      "end": 1096.16,
      "text": "a fist except for the protruding forefinger,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1096.58,
      "end": 1098.98,
      "text": "went up and then down to stop with a jerk"
    },
    {
      "start": 1098.98,
      "end": 1101.16,
      "text": "when the finger was leveled at Spade's chest."
    },
    {
      "start": 1102.54,
      "end": 1104.74,
      "text": "And you can give us the information that",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1104.74,
      "end": 1106.7,
      "text": "will enable us to determine the category."
    },
    {
      "start": 1108.416,
      "end": 1108.96,
      "text": "Spade said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1109.48,
      "end": 1110.1,
      "text": "Yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1110.48,
      "end": 1111.76,
      "text": "very slowly."
    },
    {
      "start": 1112.512,
      "end": 1114.36,
      "text": "His face was somber.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1114.82,
      "end": 1116.88,
      "text": "He touched his lower lip with the finger,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1117.08,
      "end": 1118.18,
      "text": "looked at the finger,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1118.3,
      "end": 1120.36,
      "text": "and then scratched the back of his neck with it."
    },
    {
      "start": 1121.34,
      "end": 1123.64,
      "text": "Little irritable lines had appeared in his forehead.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1124.8,
      "end": 1126.84,
      "text": "He blew his breath heavily out through his nose,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1126.94,
      "end": 1129.14,
      "text": "and his voice was an ill-humored growl."
    },
    {
      "start": 1130.23,
      "end": 1133.1,
      "text": "You wouldn't want the kind of information I could give you,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1133.16,
      "end": 1133.32,
      "text": "Brian."
    },
    {
      "start": 1133.52,
      "end": 1134.68,
      "text": "You couldn't use"
    },
    {
      "start": 1134.92,
      "end": 1135.104,
      "text": "it."
    },
    {
      "start": 1135.488,
      "end": 1138.176,
      "text": "It'd poop this gambler's revenge scenario for you.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1139.56,
      "end": 1141.7,
      "text": "Brian sat up straight and squared his shoulders.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1142.64,
      "end": 1144.74,
      "text": "His voice was stern without bluster.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1146.02,
      "end": 1147.48,
      "text": "You are not the judge of that.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1147.66,
      "end": 1149.0,
      "text": "Right or wrong,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1149.14,
      "end": 1151.12,
      "text": "I'm nevertheless the district attorney."
    },
    {
      "start": 1152.896,
      "end": 1155.0,
      "text": "Spade's lifted lip showed his eye-tooth.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1156.2,
      "end": 1158.02,
      "text": "I thought this was an informal talk.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1159.19,
      "end": 1163.02,
      "text": "I am a sworn officer of the law twenty-four hours a day,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1163.712,
      "end": 1164.14,
      "text": "Brian said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1164.84,
      "end": 1165.92,
      "text": "and neither formality"
    },
    {
      "start": 1166.02,
      "end": 1170.4,
      "text": "nor informality justifies your withholding evidence of crime from me."
    },
    {
      "start": 1170.78,
      "end": 1171.46,
      "text": "Except,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1171.7,
      "end": 1172.22,
      "text": "of course,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1172.68,
      "end": 1174.2,
      "text": "he nodded meaningly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1174.7,
      "end": 1176.6,
      "text": "on certain constitutional grounds."
    },
    {
      "start": 1178.28,
      "end": 1180.68,
      "text": "You mean if the information might incriminate me?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1181.344,
      "end": 1181.98,
      "text": "Spade asked."
    },
    {
      "start": 1183.1,
      "end": 1184.36,
      "text": "His voice was placid,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1184.38,
      "end": 1185.46,
      "text": "almost amused,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1185.52,
      "end": 1186.88,
      "text": "but his face was not."
    },
    {
      "start": 1187.92,
      "end": 1188.52,
      "text": "Well,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1188.8,
      "end": 1191.36,
      "text": "I've got grounds that suit me better than those."
    },
    {
      "start": 1192.28,
      "end": 1193.76,
      "text": "My clients are entitled to have",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1193.76,
      "end": 1195.3,
      "text": "their affairs kept confidential."
    },
    {
      "start": 1196.608,
      "end": 1198.54,
      "text": "Maybe I can be made to talk to a grand jury,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1198.82,
      "end": 1199.56,
      "text": "or even a"
    },
    {
      "start": 1199.62,
      "end": 1200.36,
      "text": "coroner's jury,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1200.56,
      "end": 1202.82,
      "text": "but I haven't been called before either yet,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1203.52,
      "end": 1204.72,
      "text": "and it's a cinch I'm not"
    },
    {
      "start": 1204.72,
      "end": 1207.48,
      "text": "going to publish any of my clients' secrets until I have to."
    },
    {
      "start": 1208.78,
      "end": 1209.14,
      "text": "Then again,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1209.34,
      "end": 1210.36,
      "text": "you and the police"
    },
    {
      "start": 1210.44,
      "end": 1213.12,
      "text": "have both accused me of being mixed up in the other night's murders."
    },
    {
      "start": 1214.432,
      "end": 1214.94,
      "text": "I've had trouble",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1215.14,
      "end": 1216.08,
      "text": "with both of you before."
    },
    {
      "start": 1217.14,
      "end": 1218.22,
      "text": "So far as I can see,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1218.6,
      "end": 1221.46,
      "text": "my best chance of clearing myself is by bringing"
    },
    {
      "start": 1221.46,
      "end": 1222.98,
      "text": "in the murderers all tied up."
    }
  ]
}